  "prompt": "What is the most underrated romantic movie?",
  "response": "The concept of the \"most underrated\" romantic movie can vary greatly depending on personal taste, but one film that often comes up in discussions is \"The Before Trilogy,\" particularly \"Before Sunrise\" (1995) directed by Richard Linklater. While the trilogy as a whole is critically acclaimed, \"Before Sunrise\" is sometimes overshadowed by more conventional romantic films. Its unique structure, focusing on a single night of conversation between two characters, Jesse and C\u00e9line, played by Ethan Hawke and Julie Delpy, offers an intimate and realistic portrayal of connection and romance. The film is praised for its authentic dialogue and the chemistry between the leads, capturing the magic and spontaneity of a chance encounter. It's a hidden gem for those who appreciate thoughtful and subtle storytelling in romance.",
